name: 7.1.0-d1
body:
**Exasol 7.1.0-d1 : Release Notes**
   docker specific fix for scriptlanguage container location

* Exasol 7.1.0 : https://www.exasol.com/portal/display/DOWNLOAD/Version+7.1.0

name: Exasol 6.1.5-d1
body:
**Exasol 6.1.5-d1 : Release Notes**

* It's now possible to set the root password when starting a container, e. g.:
  `docker run --privileged exasol/docker-db:6.1.5-d1 init-sc -n 11 --root-password strongpassword`
* Exasol 6.1.5: https://www.exasol.com/portal/display/DOWNLOAD/Version+6.1.5

name: Exasol 6.1.4-d1
body:
**Exasol 6.1.4-d1 : Release Notes**

* Each BucketFS now has an owner (and a dedicated service process)
* Exasol 6.1.4: https://www.exasol.com/portal/display/DOWNLOAD/Version+6.1.4

name: Exasol 6.1.3-d1
body:
**Exasol 6.1.3-d1 : Release Notes**

* Improved performance on NUMA architectures
* Hugepages support
* Logfile rotation
* Other performance and stability improvements
* New CLI tool `exasupport` for collecting support information
* Exasol 6.1.3: https://www.exasol.com/portal/display/DOWNLOAD/Version+6.1.3

name: Exasol 6.1.2-d1
body:
**Exasol 6.1.2-d1 : Release Notes**

* Fixed search path for database drivers (fixes #26)
* Added support for virtual network interfaces (interfaces with multiple IPs)
* Exasol 6.1.2: https://www.exasol.com/portal/display/DOWNLOAD/Version+6.1.2

name: Exasol 6.0.13-d1
body:
**Exasol 6.0.13-d1 : Release Notes**

* fixed an issue with Google Cloud instances (and netmask 255.255.255.255 in general)
* fixed Oracle driver versions in README (#24)
* newly created device files are not split into `.data` and `.meta` files anymore (only 1 file per device)
* Exasol 6.0.13: https://www.exasol.com/portal/display/DOWNLOAD/Version+6.0.13

name: Exasol 6.1.0-d1
body:
**Exasol 6.1.0-d1 : Release Notes**


* fixed an issue with Google Cloud instances (and netmask 255.255.255.255 in general)
* fixed Oracle driver versions in README (#24)
* fixed error when starting SSHd during boot sequence
* newly created device files are not split into `.data` and `.meta` files anymore (only 1 file per device)
* Exasol 6.1.0: https://www.exasol.com/portal/display/DOWNLOAD/Version+6.1.0

name: EXASOL 6.0.12-d1
body:
**EXASOL 6.0.12-d1 : Release Notes**

* fixed a bug when copying the internal EXAConf(s) back to the cluster root (on shutdown)
* fixed $PATH in the Dockerfile
* README improvements
* EXASOL 6.0.12: https://www.exasol.com/portal/display/DOWNLOAD/Version+6.0.12

name: EXASOL 6.0.11-d1
body:
**EXASOL 6.0.11-d1 : Release Notes**

* new option "AdditionalVolumes" in the "Docker" section of EXAConf (to mount user-defined volumes into the containers when using `exadt`)
* EXASOL 6.0.11: https://www.exasol.com/portal/display/DOWNLOAD/Version+6.0.11

name: EXASOL 6.0.10-d1
body:
**EXASOL 6.0.10-d1 : Release Notes**

* increased default timeout in `exadt` in order to avoid socket timeouts with `docker-py` >= 3.2.1
* fixed version check in update mechanism
* EXASOL 6.0.10: https://www.exasol.com/portal/display/DOWNLOAD/Version+6.0.10

name: EXASOL 6.0.8-d1
body:
**EXASOL 6.0.8-d1 : Release Notes**

* EXASOL 6.0.8: https://www.exasol.com/portal/display/DOWNLOAD/Version+6.0.8
* no Docker related changes

name: EXASOL 6.0.7-d1
body:
**EXASOL 6.0.7-d1 : Release Notes**

* multi-host support: standalone EXASOL containers on different hosts can now be connected to form an EXASOL cluster (see [README](https://github.com/EXASOL/docker-db/blob/master/README.md) for details)
* support for uploading custom JDBC and Oracle drivers (see [README](https://github.com/EXASOL/docker-db/blob/master/README.md) for details)
* nameservers can be specified via "NameServers" option in EXAConf
* EXAConf integrity protection mechanism using MD5 checksums. See the [README](https://github.com/EXASOL/docker-db/blob/master/README.md) 'Troubleshooting' section if you get an error after modifying EXAConf.
* EXASOL 6.0.7: https://www.exasol.com/portal/display/DOWNLOAD/Version+6.0.7

**Fixes**
* data-volumes are now created with stripe-size 256k (was 4k because of a bug)

name: EXASOL 6.0.6-d1
body:
**EXASOL 6.0.6-d1 : Release Notes**

- exadt: new parameter "--kill" for "stop-db"
- node UUID is now part of EXAConf (created during cluster initialization)
- EXASOL 6.0.6: https://www.exasol.com/portal/display/DOWNLOAD/Version+6.0.6

name: EXASOL 6.0.4-d1
body:
**EXASOL 6.0.4-d1 : Release Notes**

- new EXAConf option "Revision"
- EXASOL 6.0.4: https://www.exasol.com/portal/display/DOWNLOAD/Version+6.0.4

name: EXASOL 6.0.3-d1
body:
**EXASOL 6.0.3-d1 : Release Notes**

* new exadt command "list-dbs"
* new exadt command "collect-info" (for bug reporting,  see [README](https://github.com/EXASOL/docker-db/blob/master/README.md) for details)
* standalone EXASOL containers with persistent volumes (created with `docker run -v `) can now be updated ( see [README](https://github.com/EXASOL/docker-db/blob/master/README.md) for details).
* minor exadt improvements
* EXASOL 6.0.3: https://www.exasol.com/portal/display/DOWNLOAD/Version+6.0.3

name: EXASOL 6.0.2-d1
body:
**EXASOL 6.0.2-d1 : Release Notes**

* No more separate "self-contained" image: the standard image can now be used to create an EXASOL container with `docker run` (see [README](https://github.com/EXASOL/docker-db/blob/master/README.md) for details)
* Merged some optimizations from PR #9
* EXASOL 6.0.2: https://www.exasol.com/portal/display/DOWNLOAD/Version+6.0.2

name: EXASOL 6.0.1-d1
body:
**EXASOL 6.0.1-d1 : Release Notes**

- new exadt commands "start-db" and "stop-db": manually start and stop databases
- new exadt command "exec": execute arbitrary commands in EXASOL containers
- databases are now automatically shut down when calling "exadt stop-cluster"
- more output is visible when calling "docker logs" on an EXASOL container
- all logfiles of a virtual EXASOL cluster are now world-readable
- improved exadt Windows compatibility (fixes issue #6)
- EXASOL 6.0.1: https://www.exasol.com/portal/display/DOWNLOAD/Version+6.0.1

name: EXASOL 6.0.0-d1
body:
**EXASOL 6.0.0-d1 : Release Notes**
- initial EXASOL Docker version release
- EXASOL 6.0.0: https://www.exasol.com/portal/display/DOWNLOAD/Version+6.0.0
